<ChannelTradeLayout
  title="AI Instagram DMs for UK Structural Steelworkers | Rapid Receptionist"
  description={`AI Instagram DMs for UK structural steelworkers. Converts crane lift videos and exposed steel showcases into fabrication and erection tenders. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
  canonicalUrl="/structural-steelworkers/ai-instagram-dms/"
  channelName="AI Instagram DMs"
  tradeName="Structural Steelworker"
  tradeNamePlural="Structural Steelworkers"
  tradeSlug="structural-steelworkers"
  headline="AI Instagram DMs for UK Structural Steelwork Companies"
  accentWord="Steelwork"
  subhead="Your reel of a steel beam lift through a demolished wall earns nine thousand views. A builder DMs about RSJs for a load-bearing removal. Your AI responds while you bolt connections on site."
  scenario="It is 2am on a Saturday. A self-builder near Eynsham is designing a contemporary house with a hybrid structure — a structural steel moment frame providing the open-plan ground floor with no internal columns, supporting a timber-frame first floor and roof. The engineer has specified three moment-connected portal frames at 4-metre centres spanning 10 metres, with exposed steelwork forming the interior design feature of the double-height entrance hall. He DMs: 'Hi — building my own house with a steel moment frame ground floor. 3 frames at 4m centres, 10m span, double-height entrance. The steel will be exposed — shot-blasted with a clear lacquer finish. Engineer has designed the connections as moment frames (fully welded). Can you fabricate moment frames with exposed-quality welds? About 12 tonnes total. Eynsham area, crane access fine. Want to start foundation prep in 12 weeks.' Without AI DMs, you see the DM Saturday afternoon. Two competitors replied overnight. With AI DMs, the response lands at 2:02am: 'Thank you — we fabricate exposed-quality moment frames with dressed welds and lacquer finishes. Could you confirm the double-height dimension and whether the architect has specified the column section sizes? We will programme the fabrication sequence.' He confirms 5.5m double height and 254x254 UCs. Saturday you review: self-build, Eynsham, 3x moment frames, 10m span, 5.5m double height, 254x254 UCs, exposed shot-blasted lacquered, 12 tonnes, 12-week start."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/ai-instagram-dms/"
  tradePageUrl="/structural-steelworkers/ai-receptionist/"
  ctaHeadline="Turn Workshop Fabrication Montages into Exposed Steel Restaurant Projects"
  ctaSubhead={`A thirty-second bandsaw-to-finished-rafter reel earns eight thousand views. AI Instagram DMs converts every architect message into a tender with AESS finish and feature connections. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
/>
